r'''Step 6: To simplify further, we recognize that common factor terms should cancel out and the polynomial should emerge. We simplify each term separately:
\[
\frac{a^3 (b+c)}{(a-b)(c-a)} = \frac{a^3 (b+c)}{-(b-a)(a-c)} = \frac{-a^3 (b+c)}{(b-a)(a-c)}
\]
\[
\frac{b^3 (c+a)}{(a-b)(b-c)} = \frac{b^3 (c+a)}{-(b-a)(c-b)} = \frac{-b^3 (c+a)}{(b-a)(c-b)}
\]
\[
\frac{c^3 (a+b)}{(b-c)(c-a)} = \frac{c^3 (a+b)}{-(c-b)(a-c)} = \frac{-c^3 (a+b)}{(c-b)(a-c)}
\]'''
